properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 4 at 6:44AM CST until February 5 at 6:00AM CST by NWS Wichita KS
properties.description:
...Winter Travel impacts expected today through Wednesday...

* WHAT...periods of freezing drizzle will be possible into the
afternoon. Light snow could develop later this afternoon with
better chances late tonight. Snow accumulations are expected to
be less than an inch.

* WHERE...Sumner County.

* WHEN...until 6 AM CST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning and evening commutes.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 AM CST WEDNESDAY
